text: Slades Corners is a small unincorporated residential and agricultural community located on Old Highway 50 and 400th Avenue (Kenosha County Highway P, or Dyer Lake Road) in the southwestern Kenosha County, Wisconsin town of Wheatland.Town of Wheatland, Kenosha County, Wisconsin Slades Corners is named for Tom Slade, an early resident who settled there in approximately 1840, eight years before Wisconsin statehood.Slades Corners ==Notes== Category:Unincorporated communities in Wisconsin Category:Unincorporated communities in Kenosha County, Wisconsin
title: Slades Corners, Wisconsin
